Based on your description...

On Dec 6, 2007 12:21 PM, Lee B &lt;leeb@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt;  TestsSuperclass
&gt;  @BeforeClass
&gt;  public static void startup() {
&gt;  ...do startup stuff, using one piece of info from currently running
&gt;  subclass
&gt;  }
&gt;
&gt;  I don&#39;t see any way to get info from the subclass into that startup
&gt;  method.
&gt;

...why couldn&#39;t you do something similar to the following?  Factor the
&quot;something&quot; into a superclass static method (with a different name)
and then invoke it from a static @BeforeTest method on each subclass
(which passes the &quot;one piece of info&quot; from the subclass).

-jn-


public class SuperTest {

    public static class Info { /* whatever */ }

    public static void something(Info info) {
        // do startup stuff with info
    }

}

public class SubTest0 extends SuperTest {
    static SuperTest.Info info0 = new SuperTest.Info( /*whatever*/ );

   @BeforeClass
    public static void startup() { something(info0); }

}

public class SubTest1 extends SuperTest {
    static SuperTest.Info info1 = new SuperTest.Info(&quot;sub1&quot;);

   @BeforeClass
    public static void startup() { something(info1); }

}


